@SIGma_1296
you must be having switchable graphics which are by default set to dynamic mode. you have to set it to fixed mode, to do this go to your bios and change the opion from dynamic to fixed. In case you dont find any such option then you'll have to update your bios(i had to do it for my hp dv6 6121tx) so visit your laptop's manufacturer company's official site. Install the bios then change to fixed.then boot the system and go to that switchable graphics window it will be little different this time around make sure your active gpu is high performance .After this for sure you"ll be able to play rage and in bonus you'll get rid of that crappy switchable option. 
Hope this helps as i have spend alot of my time sorting it out
